{"id":"nexus-ku4","title":"project-level badges and scratchpad in tui","description":"Surface badges at a project level in the TUI, and include a scratch pad for ideas","notes":"## Feasibility\n- Touches: nexus-core/src/session.rs, nexus-tui/src/screens/projects.rs, nexus-tui/src/app.rs, new nexus-core/src/project.rs\n- Prior art: projects.rs already renders 7-col table (badge col follows same Row pattern); InputMode enum supports new ScratchpadEdit mode; color tokens exist\n- Blockers: No project-level metadata persistence yet; agent doesn't read .beads/; scratchpad needs tui-textarea or hand-rolled widget; detail-palette-start spec could conflict in app.rs\n- Complexity: medium — badges need agent to read .beads/ and expose via gRPC; scratchpad needs new input mode + text editor widget","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"task","owner":"leo@leonardoacosta.dev","created_at":"2026-03-20T15:55:35.241170975-05:00","created_by":"leonardoacosta","updated_at":"2026-03-20T15:55:35.241170975-05:00","labels":["idea"]}
